
[1]cozen

   COZEN, v.t.

   1. To cheat; to defraud.

   He that suffers a government to be abused by carelessness and neglect,
   does the same thing with him that corruptly sets himself to cozen it.

   2. To deceive; to beguile.

   Children may be cozened into a knowledge of the letters.
